The paper discusses a benchmarking framework for neural networks, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on performance optimization and hardware-specific analysis suggests a potential fit for computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of multiple hardware architectures and integration with frameworks like Tensorflow and Pytorch suggests a potential fit for the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category.
